<HEADLINE>
FT  15 NOV 94 / London Stock Exchange: Eurotunnel support
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER JOHN, JOEL KIBAZO and JEFFREY BROWN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Caught up in first day euphoria - direct running between London and the
Continent started officially yesterday - Eurotunnel jumped 17 to 270p amid
heavy buying from Paris and on talk that several big US hedge funds which
target high risk/high reward issues have been chasing the shares.
Their recent performance has led to head scratching among London analysts,
with the group looking increas-ingly set to miss its own severely downgraded
revenues forecast for this year. The investment approach in France has been
less fundamentally based, however.
Turnover in Paris yesterday was 3.75m shares, more than double the London
volume. Eurotunnel, under 200p less than five weeks ago, is now 5 in excess
of this year's rights issue price.
