FT  15 NOV 94 / World Commodities Prices: Tea
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
There was strong general demand this week, reports the Tea Brokers'
Association. Landed coloury Assams were again well supported at fully firm
rates. Plainer mediums met more enquiry and sometimes advanced but plainest
North Indians lost 2 to 3p. Bright and coloury medium East Africans were
generally fully firm although prices eased 2 to 3p by the close. Ceylon
bop's lost ground but the remainder were about steady with more enquiry for
pf's. Offshore good demand but at slightly easier rates. Quotations: best
available; 185p/kg, nom good; 142p/kg, good medium; 122p/kg, medium; 112p/kg
low medium; 86p, the highest price realised this week was 190p for an assam
pd.
