FT  15 NOV 94 / International Company News: JR West listing decision this
week
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TOKYO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Japan's transport ministry will decide this week whether to go ahead with
the listing of West Japan Railway (JR West) as originally planned, Reuter
reports from Tokyo.
The government is considering whether to list JR West on Japan's stock
exchanges before the end of the current fiscal year next March, transport
vice-minister Mr Michihiko Matsuo was quoted by a ministry spokesman as
telling a news conference.
'We are in a difficult situation, but we will make a decision soon, probably
by the end of this week,' Mr Matsuo was quoted as saying.
JR West applied in August to be listed on six Japanese exchanges, including
the Tokyo Stock Exchange and Osaka Securities Exchange.
Most stock market participants expect the JR West listing to be postponed
following the unsuccessful October 27 listing of another government entity,
Japan Tobacco.
