<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Bouygues, the French construction and public works group, will increase its
stake in road-building company Colas to about 60 per cent through a capital
increase and by acquiring part of an indirect stake held by the French
subsidiary of the Royal Dutch/Shell oil company, AP-DJ reports from Paris.
Colas's board decided yesterday to carry out a capital increase that will
inject between FFr700m (Dollars 133.2m) and FFr800m cash into the
road-builder and help it pursue its expansion, notably outside France,
Bouygues and Shell said in a joint statement.
At present a holding company called SITP, which is 65 per cent owned by
Bouygues and 35 per cent by Societe des Petroles Shell, controls 67 per cent
of Colas' capital.
