<HEADLINE>
FT  15 NOV 94 / International Company News: FTC to probe SmithKline purchase
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
US anti-trust authorities have launched an investigation into SmithKline
Beecham's Dollars 2.3bn acquisition earlier this year of Diversified
Pharmaceutical Services, a US drug distributor, writes Richard Waters in New
York.
The enquiry, by the Federal Trade Commission, follows its intervention last
month in Eli Lilly's purchase of PCS, a pharmacy benefit management (PBM)
company. After reaching a compromise with Lilly, the FTC said it would
continue to look closely at vertical integration in the pharmaceuticals
industry, which has seen some of the biggest distributors fall into the
hands of manufacturers.
The Diversified acquisition was completed in May, several months after Merck
paid Dollars 6.7bn for Medco Containment Services, another PBM. A Merck
spokesman could not immediately be reached, but that acquisition is also
believed to be under review.
SmithKline said that it had been notified by the FTC of its interest, and
added that 'the procedures that we have in place are responsive to any
reasonable concerns the FTC or other government representatives may have.'
</TEXT>
