FT  15 NOV 94 / Major's political secretary to leave
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Jonathan Hill is to stand down as political secretary to the prime
minister amid signs that Mr John Major wishes to revamp his team of personal
advisers in the run-up to the next election.
Mr Hill has held the job since 1992. He is one of the longest serving
members of the Downing Street staff, having been an important figure in
political strategy and planning for more than four years.
However, colleagues have said that he lacks inside experience at Westminster
and there have been indications that Mr Major is looking for a more
heavyweight figure.
Mr Hill took over as political secretary from the late Mrs Judith Chaplin,
who later became MP for Newbury. Unlike departmental special advisers, the
political secretaryship at No 10 is not a civil service post and is paid for
out of Conservative party funds.
