become increasingly intense. With its population of 9.2m, Tianjin is
stressing its huge market, skilled workforce and 'stable society and fine
public order'. However a survey of foreign investors said laws and
regulations were ignored, intellectual property protection was inadequate,
and its bureaucrats are incompetent, especially at the lower levels.
