<DATE>941115
</DATE>
<HEADLINE>
FT  15 NOV 94 / W German profits optimism
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MUNICH
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Profits in west German industry could jump 150 per cent in 1994 as a result
of economic recovery and higher productivity, according to the Munich-based
Ifo economic research institute. The institute said total profits could
surge to around DM50bn (Pounds 20.4bn) in 1994 after falling an estimated
11.9 per cent to around DM20bn in 1993. Ifo said its figures were fairly
speculative but were based on established relationships between economic
growth and production factors such as labour costs and employment levels. If
the forecasts are correct, 1994 profits would show a return to profit levels
last seen in 1989 and 1990. Ifo forecast a real improvement of 5.4 per cent
in labour productivity in 1994, the highest increase since 1979 and compared
with a 2.2 per cent rise in 1993. Unit labour costs were likely to fall 1.2
per cent in 1994 after rising 3.6 per cent in 1993 and net production in
industry was forecast to rise 3.5 per cent after falling 7.7 per cent last
year.
</TEXT>
