FT  14 NOV 94 / The Lex Column: Sweden
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The result of Sweden's referendum on EU membership yesterday should ease
pressure on government bonds and give a boost to the Stockholm stock market.
Although a Yes vote had been mostly discounted, last-minute jitters caused
by adverse opinion polls had made the markets increasingly volatile. The
expectation that EU economic convergence will force tighter control over
