<HEADLINE>
FT  14 NOV 94 / Arts (Openings): New York
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The first major American exhibition devoted to the British potters Lucie Rie
(B1902) and Hans Coper (1920-81) is being held at the Metropolitan Museum in
New York from tomorrow. Rie's refined, minimalist vessels and the sculptural
ceramic forms of Coper are among the most innovative and influential of the
century.
